(B) the Codex Vetus (containing also the first eight plays 3 see below). This is a MS. which belonged originally to some German monastery and in later times to the Library of the Elector Palatine. It is now in the Vatican Library (with shelf-mark Pal. lat. 1615). Its minuscule script of the German type is generally referred to the end of the tenth century.
